    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Sarcochilus viridiflorus are antimicrobial, exhibiting inhibition of bacterial growth and antifungal activity. Its antiviral properties demonstrate the plant's potential to combat viral infections. The analgesic and anti-inflammatory properties of Sarcochilus viridiflorus have been attributed to the presence of flavonoids, which are responsible for its pain-relieving and inflammation-reducing effects. The antioxidant properties of this plant are also associated with its ability to neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress, which is linked to the presence of phenolic compounds. The bioactive compounds, including saponins and volatile oils, contribute to its antipyretic and sedative properties, helping to reduce fever and promote relaxation.",
