    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Sarcochilus viridiflorus are flavonoids, including rutin and kaempferol, which have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, reducing inflammation and oxidative stress in the body. The plant also contains glycosides, such as sarcochiloside, which exhibit antimicrobial activity, inhibiting the growth of certain bacteria and fungi. The flavonoid quercetin, present in Sarcochilus viridiflorus, has been found to have anti-cancer properties, inhibiting cell proliferation and inducing apoptosis in cancer cells. Additionally, the plant contains phenolic acids, including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, which have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities. The combination of these constituents may contribute to the plant's potential therapeutic effects in treating various diseases.",
